------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 3A — MINI CONSULTATION STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

GOAL:
- Capture qualification inputs
- Reduce price shock later
- No persuasion
- No pricing

RULES:
- One question per turn
- One optional neutral context line
- No benefit statements
- No brand introduction unless customer triggers
- If interrupted → one fallback → then capture UNKNOWN

SEQUENCE:

Q1 (Primary Qualification)
→ Coverage / Goal Intent
   - Capture: FULL / FRONT / UNSURE
   - If price interruption → repeat once → then mark UNKNOWN

Q2 (Usage Qualification)
→ Driving usage / exposure context
   - Capture: HIGHWAY / CITY / MIXED / UNKNOWN
   - Same fallback rule

Q3 (Conditional Only)
→ Triggered ONLY if:
   - Competitor mention
   - Price pressure before 3B
   - Brand fixation
   - Capture comparison focus

PHASE 3A OUTPUT STATE:
- coverage
- usage
- brand preference (if mentioned)
- comparison focus (if triggered)
- missing fields marked UNKNOWN

Transition condition:
→ When minimum required fields captured → Move to Phase 3B


------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 3B — PRICING PRESENTATION STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

GOAL:
- Present price anchor or SKU range
- No persuasion
- No defensive justification
- One clarifier max

RULES:
- Must follow Phase 3A completion
- No stacking explanations
- No discounting
- No urgency
- One narrowing question only

STRUCTURE BLOCK:

1) Context Anchor
   - Vehicle + coverage + usage + brand (if applicable)

2) Price Exposure
   - Single range OR explicit SKU ranges
   - Derived strictly from matrix

3) Neutral Differentiation Line
   - High-level difference (durability / performance)
   - No persuasion language

4) One Steering Question
   - Brand fork OR
   - Coverage fork OR
   - Compare vs proceed fork

PHASE 3B EXIT CONDITIONS:

If customer:
- Accepts → Move to Phase 5
- Asks clarification → Clarify once (still 3B)
- Shows emotional signal → Move to Phase 4
- Goes silent → Move to Phase 4 (Silence block)


------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 4 — CONFIDENCE & SIGNAL HANDLING STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

GOAL:
- Reduce tension
- Normalize concern
- Provide micro-education
- Offer permission-based continuation
- Prevent silence

GLOBAL RULES:
- Address only ONE dominant signal
- Follow 4-step format strictly
- One question only
- No stacking
- No discount talk
- No competitor attack

UNIVERSAL PHASE 4 FORMAT:

1) Reassurance (Signal-aligned)
2) Calm normalization
3) One micro-education snippet (Core-approved)
4) Permission-based bridge:
   - Explain OR
   - Show visual proof (install example / finished vehicle)
5) Single question only

------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 4 SIGNAL PRIORITY ORDER
------------------------------------------------------------

PRICE_PRESSURE
BRAND_FIXATION
WARRANTY_SENSITIVITY
USAGE_RISK
TECHNICAL
INSTALLATION_TRUST
SILENCE

Only highest active signal handled per message.

------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 4 ESCALATION MODEL
------------------------------------------------------------

Each signal may escalate through levels:

Level 1:
- Stabilization
- Light education
- Permission bridge

Level 2:
- Deeper clarification
- Ownership context
- Permission bridge

Level 3:
- Clarified reframing
- Narrowing fork
- Permission bridge

Escalation triggered when:
- Customer repeats same signal
- Customer challenges previous clarification
- Customer compares again

------------------------------------------------------------
SILENCE HANDLING STRUCTURE
------------------------------------------------------------

Trigger:
- No response after price
- “Let me think”

Structure:

1) Calm authority opener
2) Normalize decision pause
3) Narrowing fork question
   - Brand fork OR
   - Coverage fork OR
   - Compare vs proceed fork

No price restatement.
No chasing.
No urgency.


------------------------------------------------------------
PHASE 5 TRANSITION RULE
------------------------------------------------------------

Move to Phase 5 when:
- Customer selects SKU / coverage
- Customer confirms proceed
- Customer asks booking-related question

Phase 4 must not:
- Close
- Offer discount
- Push urgency
- Negotiate

------------------------------------------------------------
DEFERRED ITEMS (NOT ALLOWED IN 3A–4)
------------------------------------------------------------

- Offers
- Discounts
- Scarcity
- Booking pressure
- Installation date discussion
- Payment plan discussion

These belong strictly to Phase 5.


============================================================
END OF PHASE 3A–4 STRUCTURE LOCK
